§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Given a ring $(R, +, ·)$ with additive group $(R, +)$. ⦉

  ‖ A subset $I ⊂ R$ is called a ❬left ideal❭ if
    𝍫 ⦊
      ‣ $(I, +)$ is a subgroup of $(R, +)$ ⦉

      ‣ $r·x ∈ I$ for every $r ∈ R$ and $x ∈ I$ ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ Similarly, it is called a ❬left ideal❭ if (2) is replaced
    with $x · r ∈ I$ for every $r ∈ R$ and $x ∈ I$. ⦉

  ‖ If $I$ is an ❬ideal❭ if it is both a left and right
    ideal. ⦉
⦉

